main event: A civilian observer reported seeing a blue-white object, approximately 30-60 feet in diameter, hovering over the trees near Duluth, Minnesota on March 6, 1963.
interesting points: The object was described as oval-shaped with a raised middle section.
The witness was a reliable person who had observed similar phenomena before.
The object hovered for a period of time before accelerating away at a high rate of speed.
No sound was reported associated with the sighting.
The witness provided a hand-drawn sketch of the object.
photographs: no, but a hand-drawn sketch was provided
